\text{Sketch and find the equations of the surfaces formed by}
\text{i) }x^2 - y^2 + 1 = 0 \text{ about the y-axis}
\text{ii) }x^2 - 2y^2 + 2a^2 = 0 \text{ about the x-axis}
\text{i) }x^2 - y^2 + 1 = 0 \text{ about the y-axis}
x(y)=\sqrt{1-y^2}
X(y,\phi)=\sqrt{1-y^2}\cos\phi
Y(y,\phi)=\sqrt{1-y^2}\sin\phi
X(y,0)=x(y)
\text{ii) }x^2 - 2y^2 + 2a^2 = 0 \text{ about the x-axis}
y(x)=\sqrt{a^2+(x^2)/2}
X(x,\phi)=\sqrt{a^2+(x^2)/2}\sin\phi
Y(x,\phi)=\sqrt{a^2+(x^2)/2}\cos\phi
Y(x,0)=y(x)
x^2-y^2+1=0
x^2+z^2
x^2
r^2=x^2+z^2
